content: Awesome

Unable to update database online it says lifetime update yet there's been one update since I got the computer version in 2015 the update was in 2017 and there has not been any update for the mobile version ever in 5 years I have had it. It is like the company is just trying to milk what money it can get out of this and I don't care to put any effort into making it better by adding new features and more stuff you could add to it
Very old version of app. Please update.

Bought the app/software for "lifetime upgrade" which seems to have been a lifespan of a nat. Hadn't updated it since I got my new mobile then realised it wasnt logged into so signed in and not only has my profile disappeared and collections left empty but seems that no one even tries to answer or help when trying to contact
Love that I can look up movies that I own on the go.

It won't update from online DB to Android. This is key if you want to keep updated on both desktop and mobile. this issue has been going on for a long time already, fix it and support your customers. In this state I advice against buying the Android version until it is fixed and working as supposed to.

A fantastic app on iPhone, a terrible app on Android. Problems: 1) U can't backup your collection to online. Backup gets halfway through and then hangs...for hours. 2) Awful clunky scrolling. Watch out for the hidden fast scroll on the right side of your collection screen, you're bound to bump it every single time you use the app & end up dozens of films from your destination. I know it's there and still knock it. Absolutely maddening. 3) No cover scrolling. Avoid ðŸ‘Ž
I'd be lost without it
Adding DVD'S is easy, updating information not so much. I tried adding a watched date to a movie and no matter what I did it would not update.

I've purchased both the PC software and Android app - and loved using the program. Problem is - the app can no longer upload to the online database. I tried clearing the online database and uploading from scratch - but no success. So right now, I just use the database on my phone to keep track of my videos. Hopefully the company will get the online database working again in the future.
Update 10/2/2020 Program seem abandoned. Some are still holding out and managing to get by... Hey, it had a good solid run. Almost 20 years...

Was great. Show all 2718 movies. Had to wipe phone clean now when i try to download it stops at 2332 and won't go any farther. Please fix. I have used this program for years and I've never had a problem.
Best $2 I ever spent.
Great way to track your DVD collection even though most people don't collect DVDs anymore
I want to print from the APP and upload images to ones that don't have one in the APP.
I've been looking for a database like this for years now that I've finally found it I am overjoyed. it does everything I wanted it to do. Well done!
I have over 2000 DVD's and this is the best way to keep them organized.
It's a good software on PC, but the app is pretty bad. It hasn't updated my online database in forever, so my PC database is obsolete. Serious lack of filters. Very disappointed now.
Love this app

Really BAD app. You can't search cast/crew or edit the collection. Can't search by region code or many other filters, and the functionality/layout is poor, aged and lackluster in general. The Invelos owner, Ken Cole, has jumped ship long ago. Inexcusable and pathetic! This means no more updates ever for PC or mobile, until someone else takes over. I'm what you could call a power user of this database software since +10 years and nowadays it's just us that keep all of it running. Screw you, Ken!
I paid the app, but my registration suddenly dissapeared. Can't update or access my database anymore. Absolutely no response from support. This is not acceptable.

I chose this app over "My Movies" so I could upload and customize movies not found in a database. It seems I cannot add cover art or details without paying an additional 15$ for web based support. Also, My Movies has a better barcode scanner and database. For 3$ the app is good for cataloging movies. I wanted a few more options.
looked nice tried numerous dad's would not read barcoded
Excellent app. Have collectoon everywhere I go

i really liked this app. Until i got a new phone and wasn't able to retrieve it. i emailed invelos several times , no response. i paid for the app again. Was able to log in to my old account but have not been able to successfully retrieve my library. i have more than 1800 titles . i don't wish to have to scan them again . I wish invelos had responded to my emails. Very poor customer service.
Literally doesnt show collection, its primary function
The best DVD/Blu-ray collection database manager out there, period.
a lot of movies are not in the database

Bought this as had same one on my old iPhone for free as I've now changed to android with over 472 dvds on my online profile and buying more dvds I thought it best to keep it up to date again so I bought this app and downloaded it. I logged back into my profile where I could see the amount I had uploaded so decided to sync it to my new phone and found out after All morning trying to download it from my profile that it does not work. Why is this still available to purchase. Refund me
All the hoopla in the description about how powerful and flexible it is, I figured it would import/export. Nope. Not gonna mess around with all that data-entry nonsense to get all my movies into it.

this app has been locking up for almost 2 years and i havent been able to update my online collection since the spring of 2017. Several people have had similar problems, but the company has not responded. this was the best option I've seen for tracking your collection, but if you can no longer update your collection then its pretty well worthless. If this issue was fixed I'd choose this one over any other, but for now, its the worst of the bunch.
Needs a Blu ray/4K/3D update but still a great reliable app.

An absolutely fabulous app for working with my database of all my movies and TV series etc. This is of course the companion app that works with the full-blown DVD Profiler PC software and I have this app installed on my mobile phone and tablet to allow me to work with the database. Since buying both the app and the Windows software I have used a cheap barcode scanner to enter my collection with great ease. The online database from which you can download data for your films etc. is huge. The degree to which DVD Profiler allows for detailed entries is second to none. Customisation features etc. are just amazing too. I honestly urge you to give the PC software a go first then use this app to access your database and perform various actions. Very highly recommended!
Great addition to PC version.
Keeps crashing

After using this app for years, I went into it today to check if a movie was in my collection, and none of my movies display. It still reports the number of movies I have, so the database isn't completely broken, but it is essentially useless now.
Using it for years 3900 DVDs

If the list was updated so I didn't have to manually input really obvious films that it should find I'd give more stars, it finds all my low budget films no problem but struggles to find new releases and big budget films, such as lord of the rings extended discs!
Great app used the desktop software for years as well

Perfect app for your whole dvd/blu ray collection to use  on your mobile Phone. Easy transfer via your DVD Profiler online collection. Only a shame that it won't support Laserdiscs i have a lot of those to..

I had the app in my ipad and it was great but when i switch to my android 
is refusing to download....really frustrated with it lately. :(
Great app for your collection!
Since update app fails when try to download list online
Have to turn iff Invelos update to get profile upload to work. Otherwise, app works well. Very annoying.
changed phones now it refuses to download more than half my collection...all that time, wasted.
Amazing app! I have over 2000 movies. This app is a must for any movie collector!
No longer updates, even tried it on a new device but does not complete download.

I've been using DVD Profiler for years, but as of today (March 3, 2018) support for the app and program seems to have vanished. Database won't update, can't enter new titles and Invelos's website is gone from the Net. After spending so much time cataloging my collection, it's depressing to think that I've got to find another app and start from square one again.
Tried to sync up my collection of 1000+ movies for 3 hours and nothing.  This app is garbage.

I think this app is great. Had it for awhile. What I don't get is why after 600 plus movies the database won't update anymore? It sticks there saying updating but never finishes. Reinstalled and added all my movies manually again. Takes hours and hours to do this. Would always update until 600+ are catalogued then it stops database updating again. Arrrgh! Still let's me add movies but won't update. I bought this app and figured it would be awesome. I don't get it. 5 stars if this is fixed or someone tells me what's wrong.
I tried to add a few new DVDs to my collection and went from 151 to 0. It ate my entire collection, this program is absolutely worthless

Just installed on Samsung Galaxy 7 with Android version 7. Hit the Help button to show how to set up Sync. If the Windows Firewall screen pops up then "allow connection",  if you can't see the connection button at the top of the screen when you get to that stage in the help instructions on your phone, just back out until you get back to the connection settings and fill them in.  From then on Plain Sailing so long as the firewall is allowed.  Well impressed so far. Perfect sync!  I synced with my PC not online!
Can no longer update my database from the app.
Syncs with PC version without a problem.  Would be good to have ability to have more than 2 level deep for a box set.
Best application to keep track of a large dvd collection. I love it. Absolutely worth buying!!!
This was a great app that no longer works for me....I'm unable to upload my database, frustrating. It just hangs on updating profile...I sent in help request and no answer....

Hundreds of titles I added to my collection have disappeared. Many titles are absent from the publisher's database, and there is no way to submit corrections or new entries. The ability to create a new entry in the app is very limited. Adding a boxset doesn't include the contained titles as a nested listing; you must search for them & add them individually, that is, if they are present in the publisher's database. As a standalone app it is a waste of time and money.
Downloaded my database perfectly.  Love the app
Sinds laatse updat kan ik mijn films niet meer uploaden...
Can't download my collection to my new phone.
Can't import libraries to new phone from old just frustrating hot garbage
I love this i bought the pc version but the android version of this keeps force closing everyother time when i try to update my database?
Can't connect to the onlinebackup. Waste since years!
Don't believe nay sayers backed up collection to my invelos account installed software on new device logged back into account and whole collection restored.

You can't beat this app. For someone with a large collection, it's most handy having this in your pocket to quickly access your collection at any time, if you're unsure of a particular title is in your collection. Highly recommend!
An amazing app! I've changed android phones a few times and all updates and loads fine. Great dvd database for your collection.

The data from my collection of approx 1600 titles is bloating this app out to nearly 500mb! I also bought MyMovies Pro and whilst that app is marginally less attractive it manages to hold the same information in under 50mb! Unless I'm doing something drastically wrong, this is unacceptable.
Loved it, until I upgraded my HTC  One M9, now it won't let me connect with my PC  database, PLEASE FIX
Reliable and simple. All functions work perfectly for me. Samsung Note 4. Saves me buying movies I already own. Lol. A great resource.

Great product.   Barcode to title is better than I expected.   Where three movie pack forms part of the title does not list individual movies in database.   When it comes to custom entries the ability to do a little bit more customization would be good, eg add a pic of the cover.
PC sync is a joke. Initial import takes forever and God beware your phone falls asleep while doing it then you have to try it again.
Works better than my desktop version, mainly because I can scan UPC's
Deletes items at random....    Removes titles.     It dropped roughly 20 blu rays from my list recently.
Won't download and store my movies on my phone. Shows 0 in my collection. Please contact me.
The option to have multiple lists would be a bonus, I want to keep my dvds, blurry, and TV shows separate

I really enjoy being able to scan new movies into the collection. I find updating the website from the PC first time you update the app, then use the phone to scan in New items.  Up to the website, then down to the PC.
Awesome and fast!
Says I'm not connected to internet so it won't load by barcode. How did I post this review?

The app simply doesn't work properly on my Nexus 7. The PC version of DVD Profiler is good but the app is useless and as far as I'm concerned it was a waste of money. Many people have complained about problems but there seems little help.

After scanning in my collection, the app promptly failed. It cannot be uploaded or downloaded. The developer provides no support and cares so little about the app (other than taking your money), it will not even get the app to function to sell more products! Buy a different database that it's developer cares to make it function as advertised. ,.
Managed to sync with my collection, but I find it a little unintuitive. Hopefully I don't purchase any more duplicate DVDs.

Don't waste your money, got a new phone, I transferred the database to my PC and the SD card on the old phone. Downloaded the app to my new phone, transferred the backed up database to the internal storage of the new phone and placed the old phones SD card (with the back up) in the new phone. Opened the app and nothing showed up, there is NO option to restore a database from a backup.  How unprofessional! When I went back to the old phone, thinking that the database would still be on it, that database was missing/wiped, nothing! Piece of crap!
So frustrating.

I paid for the Windows version years ago, and the Android version as soon an it became available. There are several counterintuitive UI aspects in both versions, but nothing that can't be worked out with some effort.

I like that I can access my account and collection. My computer died so I paid for and installed this program to view and print my collection. It states in order to print I need to have the computer version up and running so that my phone can connect to it and print. Why did I have to pay for this app if I have to use the full computer version to do what I need? $2.99 was highway robbery for an app that is not full fledged functional. Basically this is a trial version of the app.
Niquel sur le galaxy s 3

Got this as its the only program that doesn't need a network to view your collection (sort it apps does need it, dvd library dont) but is able to run on my tablet and desktop (windows and linux via WINE). Nice printing templates and syncing options for devices makes this a Swiss army knife of cataloging no matter the device. Only gripe is no editing the movie info when adding via a barcode on my phone.  For now I scan on my phone and edit it on the windows app. When this feature is added (I am hoping lol) a 5-star rating would be no issue!

I was so excited to get this sip...but it went install on my devices. I wasted time...energy and money. I only got one star because it activated the comment! Save yourself! Don't bother. So DISAPPOINTED.
Needs a quicker way to add movies to list.
Brilliant piece of kit. In depth or simple formats.  Definitely coming with me when I go to cex hmv fopp etc. To check I don't buy discs we have already.
I've been using this app for a long time and it has always served me well. Thank you for providing a useful and reliable product.

I tried to use the custom entry feature for a few movies that weren't in database. The movie was added to my list but it deleted the previous movie that was added using custom entry. Also would like to be able to edit in more fields than just the notes field.

I'm really disappointed with this app. I bought it to keep track of the movies I loan out but the return function is worthless. In order to get a movie off my loaned list, I have to delete it from my collection and re-add it. I wish I hadn't spent my money on this.
Great way to keep track of DVD and Blu-ray

I'm glad I bought this half price. It installs ok but its impossible to download my collection onto my android device either wirelessly or via cable. The "Help" guide is incomplete and refers to buttons that do not exist.  A waste of Â£2
Been using DVD profiler for years. Please make multiple local and online accounts possible.
Its a perfect addition to the Desktop Version. Nice to have you collection with you. I love it !
first  rate app for dvd records
I have the windows version of this. The app feels a little bit unintuitive to use. The layout and style of the interface could do with some improvement too.

As an owner of the pc version this is a must have. Take your collection with you and never buy a duplicate again. Simply scan new additions with your phone and sync to update the pc database. Just brilliant software for the medium to advanced users who love their movies.

Provides stable, reliable and entirely accurate access to the PC version. Easy and nearly automated sync your database in either direction. Speedily enter all your DVD titles by scanning the UPC codes.

Very handy app, I have a large collection but I usually know if I have a movie or not but it is good to be able to check when you are at the shop and don't want to miss out on a deal.  It is also good to have your movie data base with you when you are talking movies and you know the actors name or movie but you just cant recall it at that very second.  App runs well, I have no complaints. Samsung Galaxy S GT-S7562.

...this software is lacking.  Apparently you need to invest an additional $30 for the desktop version for any customization abilities.  Even tags cannot be created without it.  I was very quickly and extremely disappointed.

Most items on my list don't have pictures even though the item listing does have a picture.... even then the pictures don't always show on the item listings. Also crashes every time I try to add an items to my list and can't register anything as watched. Don't have pc version. Phone running Android 5.0 Lollipop. Annoyed that an app that cost nearly Â£5 doesn't even work properly.

Have had the PC version for years and it has been an awesome tool. Finally I see the Android version and can't wait to get it for my phone. It keeps crashing while trying to sync with my PC database. What a waist of $7. They need to create a converter for the PC database file over to android instead trying to sync them.
Perfect app
Having a DVD collection, in excess of 1250 movies, right in my phone has prevented dozens of duplicate purchases!  I highly recommend it to anyone with a DVD collection.
.... would like to scale the size of the covers in the cover view
Have tried both Computer Name and the I.P. Address and neither one works
Can't make changes to collection view. It is cut off .

I have the PC version of this and I have installed the app on my phone and tablet.  I use the app to scan the barcodes and then sync to the PC version, this saves time when scanning multiple titles.  Both the PC and app are well worth the money.
I've been using this software for years and the app is a great piece of the puzzle. I use it constantly to check my collection and add new titles on the fly. Highly recommended.
I've been using DVD Profiler since back when Windows phones were in style. My DVD collection couldn't  be any more organized.
Absolutely, without question, the best program of its kind.

Invelo's DVD Profiler for Android is a welcome product and an excellent companion to the desktop application.  Heck, you don't even require the full-blown desktop app to use this.  I have no doubt that Ken will continue to develop and improve this as we move forward and I look forward to the enhancements that are to come!
Works well the best on the market
The perfect companion to the pc version. Easy database update and very easy handling. Pics look great.
I just wish it offered a report option and a few widgets would be great.
Never had any problems and it's great to have all the information related to my collection at my fingertips.

It works well after the initial sync with your PC or online collection. Crashed several times while downloading an admittedly large collection. But after that worked well. Easy to add by scanning barcode. Wish there were more details like the PC version and I wish I could update cover scans through the phone. Those additions would raise it to 5 stars in my mind.
Works great for me!

userName: Robert A Crowe Mobile Home Workshop
content: Love it but would like to see on the loan dvd page the ability to send text messages also for loan return

I have used the PC version for years and figured it was time to try the Android version. I can configure, but cannot download my collection from Invelos. I guess I'll have to try straight from the PC, but this was a big bummer.

Update gave it another chance and it won't find some of my movies and movies that it should easly find keeps crashing cant do anytging well  Igot screwed by a product  Iheard alot a good about im going back to MY,MOVIES
Loved it

I've used the PC version for years and find this invaluable to be able to take details of my collection with me. Using it on an Xperia Z and it is far easier than opening the uploaded online discs in a browser, despite the large screen of that phone. I do seem to remember some frustrations with getting it to sync originally but once I'd set a static IP address for the PC it was fine. Very happy I bought it.
Makes it easy to track and not duplicate your collection. Uses my phone's camera so no longer need a bar code scanner that I have to go back and download.
The easiest way for me to keep my enormous movie collection catalogued. I also like how it keeps track of who I've loaned movies to.
Using on the S4 and no problems. Took a long time to get the android version out but glad I waited. Been using the desktop version for a long time and didn't want to start over.
I cannot get it to download my collection. Always crashes. Was able to last update in January. Even upgraded to latest version today and keeps crashing.   Love the PC app, hate the Android app.
Couldnt share this on more than in device and cant back up online

I have been using this for years. I keep only my horror and sci-fi discs listed and it is a great tool for showing friends what you have and knowing if you should buy the movie you just found at the store or not because you already have it. Terrific!

Invelos DVD Profiler - I have used full program foWindows on my PC & for my iphone. Enhancements over the years have improved the ease of use dramatically on the phone. Now have android & read complaints of problems but mine installed properly & it's fantastic -.
Very buggy. Keeps crashing
I've used the PC version for years and it's wonderful to have the complete collection synced on the phone too.
This App worked perfectly until my phone updated to KitKat. Now all I get is "unfortunately DvdProfiler has stopped working" and the App crashes. Please cotrect this error as I use this App a lot.

I have the Galaxy S5 and this app works perfectlyâ€”No problems at all! Not the most attractive set up and there are a few cosmetic issues like manually hiding the keyboard after a search.  Otherwise this app is the almost perfect companion to the PC program.

I have used the pc version for years so when this came out I thought great I'll have it on the go as well. But every time I sync my collection and then try to view on my phone, or freezes and I have to do a hard reset. Hope they do an update soon to fix it.
Since yesterday it keeps on saying dvd profiler has stopped,  can't open up
Great app but constantly crashing. Crashes every few minutes while inputting movies.

I enjoy this app for cateloging my movies... but after forgetting to add for over a couple years I have well over several hundred DVDs to add. PLEASE  add a mass add feature for scanning the UPC of multiple movies *fast*. The normal scan process takes forever when I have a huge collection.
Uses online collection.  Very easy you sync and use.
Constantly force closes and will not sync to the cloud. Overall, poor experience. Also, would not save to the external SD card, regardless of the settings selected.
I would rate this app a 5 if it had searchable formats other than DVD or Blu-ray such as mp4, wmv, cloud or ultra violet.

App on 4.4 Tablet crashes when updating collection. 4.3 phone updates fine but with current options phone can't take the size of the images (and this is on the low res setting). Needs smaller/fewer images or option for none (or ideally to reuse the thumbnails in the detail screen) as any decent sized collection (mine is 2000) will cause issues, and isn't it people with large collections who buy an app/program like this in the first place?

App es working OK n and dive I got my Android OS upgrades in my S4 it just don't work when I try to item my collection I get "unfortunately DVD profile stopped working"  Fix this App and I'll change my rate

This app worked perfectly for me on my GS4 version 4.3. Installed the new software version 4.4 and now I can't do anything. It crashes every time I try to do something. Fix the crash problem and I'll give it 5 stars but till then, stay away.

I've been using DVD profiler for about 8 years now and it is by far the best DVD/Blur-ray Collection DB out there.  I had used the IOS version of DVD profiler with minimal success.  When I ditched IOS for good and went Android i was itching for DVD profiler to make its way on the Android Store.  When it did it did not disappoint.  I was able to sync my DB with NO ISSUES after setting up DVD profiler on my PC.  If anyone has issues you should consider going to the DVD profiler forums BEFORE rating it any less then 4 stars.  The rating system is based on how well the program works.  People rating on the sole fact that they are not able to setup their connection properly need to realize that is not the fault of the app.  The only issue I've had with the app is the barcode scanner sometimes is faulty.

I've very happily used DVD Profiler on my PC for... over ten years now, I think; and I've waited eagerly for this app.  It doesn't disappoint. I had no trouble setting it up; neither on my old HTC Thunderbolt, nor  my recently purchased Galaxy S4. Took a long time to transfer my collection initially, but I have 2900+ titles now, and I'd say the time it takes is actually very reasonable!  I could change a couple things, but they're minor!  Overall, I love this app! Far better and easier than the competition!
Crashes everytime I try to sync to my online DB. Rip off.
This is the best one I have found easy to use both on mobile device and pc.  Just too long in getting here.
Have been waiting this for a  long time. It works grate. I am using online sync.
great dvd manager i have all three versions of it

The app is imature, but has a lot  of potensial and a very good companion to the windows program.  Adding titles to your collection is much faster using your phone as a scanner. Finding a title for the evening is much more practical.

I have tried virtually every dvd cataloging app on here, and so far, with 220 of my 960 dvds entered, I have no real complaints. It has done a couple of spontaneous quits, but immediately picked up where it left off, so it's not too frustrating.  In my opinion, this is the best app available for people wanting to catalog their movies on android. And it can only get better from here. For the record, I am using it on a Samsung Galaxy Tab 3 8". It looks great on it.
Great for archiving collection

This app on paper is good but if u have more than a few dvds it's completely useless. There is NO batch adding, unlike movie collector. So this means if you, like me, have hundreds of dvds you have to individually add them. The second issue is that the app crashes every time I go to loggin to sync with my pc, every time, no exceptions. I made the mistake of buying both the app and the pc program off good reviews. If I could get my money back I would. Be warned, do not buy the PC version or the app.
Common titles have no imported info what so ever. I would at least like to have the option to put that info in myself.
Tried the other Free ones and are worthless.  This app is well worth the money if u keep a large dvd collection. Samsung Galaxy

I tried a couple times to update to my Galaxy S4, but it wouldn't connect to the server. As soon as I replaced the "Shared on" from the name of the computer to the IP address, it updated everything perfectly and quickly. This is great. I've been using the desktop program for well over a year, and finally decided to give myself the Android version as a Christmas present. It's great to be able to take the list of all our movies along when we're shopping...I know there have been several times when we missed out on a sale because we were sure we already owned a movie.  There are a nice set of options for how you view and browse your database.   If you're familiar with and like the desktop version, you really must have this app.
I love this app. I have the desktop application also and they work great together.    It is cool to have my collection on a portable device. I would recommend getting this app.
Easy to use and shiny, too.

I rarely pay for apps and I regret this purchase. The concept is great but the execution...not so much. App freezes and quits whenever I try to do anything. Also there is no batch add, you can see how time consuming that would be if you own hundreds of DVDs
Great app, easy to use
Now I can reference my collection on the road. Thank you!
Paid and cannot even update my collection!!

I have used DVD Profiler for about 10 years on my compters and my old PDA and Windows phone. I had just decided to give up and buy some other app. I am now VERY HAPPY! There are a few things I'd change, but overall, nice job. My 800+ DVDs and I are looking forward to an improved relationship.
Finally as useful as its online predecessor.

I have been using pc and iOs version of this app for a while,  and was happy that this finally arrived. I use galaxy note 8 and had no problems synch it to my pc version. Few things that I like on iOs are missing on this android version. 1. Using the tablet in landscape orientation did not give us the scrollable covers, which I liked. 2. In the normal orientation, when viewing movie cover, I could not scroll again. Had to go back to catalog screen then view covers. This is tedious.
I use this on my pc as well downloaded the app and it syncs with my online account so i dont keep buying dvds and blu-rays I already own

This is one of the easier programs to scan in your DVDs (I scanned in 1097 titles in 2 days). It organizes them for you nicely, but I can't get it to sync to my online account. The program keeps stopping. I just hope they fix it soon and nothing happens to my phone in the meantime....
Fantastic app.  Integrates well with the desktop application.
Crashes when logging in to online account, and scanning bar codes. Missing artwork.
Been using the pc version for years.  Nice to have my collection in my hands whenever I need it. Worth the money.
Great app!
Was nice when it first came out, now just blah. No updates in months, seems to be an abandoned app. Oh well....

I used DVD Profiler on Windows for years and I love browsing it before a movie evening to select the movie fitting to my mood. Until now I need to fire up my PC. I envied the apple users for getting access from their devices. Finally on android; and what a start: Despite having a version 1.0.1 the app worked like charm on the first try. If you are a fan of DVD profiler and own an Android device: Buy it, worth every cent. If you never heard of DVD profiler for managing your Blu Ray and DVD collection: Give it a chance.

I just bought the app and can't even get it to connect. Taking over an hour and still trying to connect. Sharing is allowed and all fields are correctly filled in. Don't know what to do if i can't even connect to my pc to update the database.

I had this app on iOS before and was able to add artwork,  edit titles etc on this android version you can't do any of that. You can't even change the frigging background.   App also occasionally crashes when trying to add a new title.   When you charge this much for an app you should be able to back that up with quality.   Sort it out

I own about 800 dvds and this app is ok it forces close all the time while I'm adding movies and with the thumbnail view on your library scrolling down it'll go a cookoo so they have some work to do. So I would say don't buy this app not what you're expecting.

I've been using dvdp for win mobile and pc for years..Those are great apps. This one not so much. Not only does it keep disconnecting ( you can only update through wifi to pc or online ) it takes days to update a first run if you have a big ( mine was about 6000 movies)..It took me 4 days with all the disconnects to update my profile..It was all saved to an sd card in my phone. Had to do a reset on the phone and now I have to go through the whole process again because you can't open a database that you saved to an sd card apparently..I haven't been able to figure out how anyway,,,And this things crashes constantly..Not very stable if you ask me...I'd say skip it till the program gets better

It took me nearly an entire day to figure out how to get this app to communicate with my PC and how to get the database to save to the external SD drive on my phone instead of the internal memory.  (I selected external SD when I installed the app but it ignored my selection and ended up using all of my phone's internal memory).  Once I actually got it working, however, I ended up liking it a lot.  My whole movie database is on my smartphone with covers and when I'm shopping at Half Prices Books and see something I'm not sure whether or not I already have, I can check my phone.  While transferring the initial database from your PC to the phone memory takes forever (assuming you already have DVD Profiler on your PC) once the database is actually on your phone updating changes between the phone and PC versions is actually pretty quick since it only updates the changes, not the whole database.  I think Invelos needs to make set-up easier but otherwise I like the app.

I was stunned to find out that I basically cannot edit a friggin thing in this app.  I had to add a custom entry, which I thought, no problem I'll just fill in all the information myself. Well, i was able to add the title and UPC, that is it!  I thought this was a top tier catalog app?  I cannot add cover artwork to my custom entry, can't add cast, crew, synopsis, etc.  This app is basically useless to me now that I know I cannot edit anything.  And the stupid Invelos is bad too.  I'll keep looking.
